http://www.json.org/ shows that the string of a 
            {
                string:value
            }
             pair inside an object must have quotes around it,
             yet your api isn't following that (see your example above) - and that's causing PHP's json_decode function to return NULL.


            {
                 name: “Joe Doe”,
                 title: “VP,
                 Engineering”,
                 phone: “13-456-7890″
            }
              should be


            {
                 "name": “Joe Doe”,
                 "title": “VP,
                 Engineering”,
                 "phone": “13-456-7890″
            }

[
    ...
]
